The paper deals with a data structure for range reporting queries, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely categories. The paper also mentions the Weber-Fechner Law, which is related to human perception and interpretation of data, suggesting a possible connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of weights and ranks in the data structure may also relate to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
